// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
// DPM built-in trust set resource.
//
// Embeds dpm-trust-set.yaml as DPM_TRUST_SET / YAML so every dpm.exe and
// DPM.IDE.*.dll binary carries a copy of the default trust pins, default
// validation mode, and emergency-revocation list at startup.
//
// Linked by DPM.Core.Trust.TrustSet via `{$R}` directive — see that unit
// for the resource-name and type the loader expects (DPM_TRUST_SET, YAML).
//
// Update flow:
//   1. Edit dpm-trust-set.yaml (bump dpmTrustSetVersion).
//   2. Rebuild — via brcc32
//   3. Ship. Existing receipts on user machines will detect the new
//      fingerprint and re-verify on next install.
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

DPM_TRUST_SET YAML "dpm-trust-set.yaml"
